    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is structured into thematic, full-screen sections to guide the user on a journey from problem to solution. This non-linear, scannable format is better than a simple text document for a business leader audience who may want to jump to specific points of interest like ROI or Integrations. The flow is: Hero (Intro) -> The Challenge (Problem Visualization) -> The Solution (AetherFlow's automated workflow) -> Value & ROI (Interactive dashboard) -> AI-Powered Blueprint -> Integrations (Interactive discovery) -> CTA. This structure breaks down complex information into digestible, interactive chunks, enhancing comprehension and engagement. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - The Challenge: Report Info -> Disconnected, manual onboarding process. Goal -> Organize/Illustrate complexity. Viz/Method -> Interactive diagram with HTML/CSS/JS. Interaction -> Hovering over roles (HR, IT) reveals specific pain points. Justification -> Visually communicates the core problem more effectively than text alone.
        - Value & ROI: Report Info -> Time savings, cost efficiency, productivity gains. Goal -> Compare/Quantify benefits. Viz/Method -> Interactive bar chart (Chart.js) with sliders. Interaction -> User adjusts sliders for # of new hires and staff cost, chart dynamically updates to show cost savings. Justification -> Personalizes the value proposition, making the ROI tangible and impactful.
        - AI-Powered Blueprint: Report Info -> The AI-driven nature of AetherFlow. Goal -> Demonstrate the product's intelligence. Viz/Method -> Text input and button to call the Gemini API. Interaction -> User enters a job role, and the app generates a detailed onboarding blueprint. Justification -> Directly demonstrates the core AI capability of the product, moving from a static claim to a live, engaging experience.
        - Integrations: Report Info -> Long list of integrations. Goal -> Organize/Inform. Viz/Method -> Interactive hub-and-spoke diagram (HTML/CSS/JS). Interaction -> Clicking on a system category (e.g., CRM) displays specific platform logos and details. Justification -> Manages a large amount of information without overwhelming the user, allowing for self-directed exploration.
        - All other content is presented in clean, scannable cards and text blocks to support the main interactive elements. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
